IRS990.Desc: FEEDING TEXAS FUNDS THE DISTRIBUTRIBUTION OF FOOD THROUGH MEMBER FOOD BANKS TO SERVE NEEDY OR LOW-INCOME INDIVIDUALS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: FEEDING TEXAS FUNDS APPLICATION ASSISTANCE TO INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE POTENTIALLY ELIGIBLE FOR HHSC SOCIAL SERVICE PROGRAMS INTERNALLY AND THROUGH MEMBER FOOD BANKS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: FEEDING TEXAS FUNDS PROGRAMS INTERNALLY AND AT MEMBER FOOD BANKS WITH A GOAL OF IMPROVING THE LIKELIHOOD THAT PERSONS ELIGIBLE FOR SNAP AND OTHER FOOD INSECURE INDIVIDUALS WILL MAKE HEALTHY FOOD CHOICES WITHIN A LIMITED BUDGET AND CHOOSE PHYHSICALLY ACTIVE LIFESTYLES.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: THE REMAINDER OF PROGRAM SERVICES WERE EXPENDED TO FURTHER THE MISSION OF FEEDING TEXAS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FEEDING TEXAS IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAXES UNDER INTERNAL REVENUE CODE SECTION 501(C)(3) AND IS CLASSIFIED AS A NONPROFIT ORGANIZATION. ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES HAS BEEN MADE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. TAXES ARE PAID ON NET INCOME EARNED FROM SOURCES UNRELATED TO THE EXEMPT PURPOSES. THERE WAS NO NET INCOME FROM UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME FOR THE YEARS ENDED SEPTEMBER 30, 2022 AND 2021. FEEDING TEXAS HAS ADOPTED FASB ASC740, ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAX. THE BENEFIT OF A TAX POSITION IS RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IN THE PERIOD DURING WHICH, BASED ON ALL AVAILABLE EVIDENCE, MANAGEMENT BELIEVES IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE POSITIONS WILL BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION, INCLUDING THE RESOLUTION OF APPEALS OR LITIGATION PROCESSES,IF ANY. TAX POSITIONS THAT MEET THE MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT RECOGNITION THRESHOLD ARE MEASURED AS THE LARGEST AMOUNT OF TAX BENEFIT THAT IS MORE THAN 50% LIKELY OF BEING RECOGNIZED UPON SETTLEMENT WITH THE APPLICABLE TAXING AUTHORITY. AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2022, FEEDING TEXAS HAS NOT RECOGNIZED LIABILTIIES FOR UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS OR ASSOCIATED INTEREST AND PENALTIES. FEEDING TEXAS'S TAX RETURNS ARE SUBJECT TO REVIEW AND EXAMINATION BY FEDERAL AND STATE AUTHORITIES. TAX RETURNS ARE OPEN FOR EXAMINATION BY THESE AUTHORITIES FOR THREE YEARS FROM THE DUE DATE OF THE RETURN OR THE DATE ACTUALLY FILED. AS OF SEPTEMBER 30, 2022, THE TAX RETURN YEARS OPEN FOR EXAMINATION INCLUDE TAX YEARS ENDED SEPTEMBER 30, 2019, AND AFTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HHSC FUNDS ARE PROVIDED TO FOOD BANKS ON COST REIMBURSEMENT BASIS. ACCOUNTANT AND CFO REVIEW AND APPROVE REIMBURSEMENT REQUESTS. TDA FUNDS ARE DISBURSED BASED ON COSTS INCURRED AND BILLED BY CFP. ACCOUNTANTS PROCESS VENDOR INVOICES, AND ENTER THEM FOR PAYMENT.
SALARY OF THE CEO/EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR IS SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH POSITION IS SCORED IN A COMPENSATION MATRIX AND POSITIONS WITH THE SAME SCORE RECEIVE THE SAME SALARY. INFORMATION ABOUT MARKET RATES IS REVIEWED TO HELP DETERMINE SALARIES. CEO & CFO SALARIES ARE APPROVED BY THE BOARD DURING THE BUDGETING PROCESS. OTHE SALARIES ARE APPROVED BY THE CEO USING THE COMPENSATION MATRIX. ALL SALARIES ARE DISCLOSED TO THE BOARD AND APPROVED WITH THE BUDGET.
